item.title: [CASSANDRA-20338] Multiple single-node SAI query bugs relating to static columns and indexed partition key elements

item.summary: Multiple single-node SAI query bugs relating to static columns and indexed partition key elements

status.description: A resolution has been taken, and it is awaiting verification by reporter. From here issues are either reopened, or are closed.

comments.comment:
I have not been able to reproduce this on the history above in a plain, single-node CQLTester test (or an equivalent in-JVM test).

@Test
public void test20338()
{
    createTable("CREATE TABLE %s (pk0 double,  pk1 text, ck0 ascii, s0 time static, s1 boolean static, v0 varint,  v1 bigint,  v2 'org.apache.cassandra.db.marshal.LexicalUUIDType', v3 double, v4 ascii, PRIMARY KEY ((pk0, pk1), ck0))" +
                " WITH CLUSTERING ORDER BY (ck0 ASC)" +
                " AND compaction = {'class': 'org.apache.cassandra.db.compaction.SizeTieredCompactionStrategy', 'max_threshold': '32', 'min_threshold': '4'}\n" +
                " AND compression = {'chunk_length_in_kb': '16', 'class': 'org.apache.cassandra.io.compress.LZ4Compressor'}");

    createIndex("CREATE INDEX tbl_pk0 ON %s(pk0) USING 'sai'");
    createIndex("CREATE INDEX tbl_pk1 ON %s(pk1) USING 'sai'");
    createIndex("CREATE INDEX tbl_ck0 ON %s(ck0) USING 'sai'");
    createIndex("CREATE INDEX tbl_s0 ON %s(s0) USING 'sai'");
    createIndex("CREATE INDEX tbl_s1 ON %s(s1) USING 'sai'");
    createIndex("CREATE INDEX tbl_v0 ON %s(v0) USING 'sai'");
    createIndex("CREATE INDEX tbl_v1 ON %s(v1) USING 'sai'");
    createIndex("CREATE INDEX tbl_v3 ON %s(v3) USING 'sai'");
    createIndex("CREATE INDEX tbl_v4 ON %s(v4) USING 'sai'");

    execute("INSERT INTO %s (pk0, pk1, ck0, s0, s1, v0, v1, v2, v3, v4) VALUES (1.0844396412062203E195, '蚨㡦Ɱ擳麗㾢鉦鵅', 'Q', '14:59:24.557825178', false, 21 * -126, -3909575580531410414, 0x0000000000001d008e00000000000000, 1.3611534850564156E135 - -1.3619298083760226E-178, '0c\u0011?\u007Fm[' + 'on]50h') USING TIMESTAMP 4");
    execute("DELETE FROM %s USING TIMESTAMP 5 WHERE  pk0 = 1.0844396412062203E195 AND  pk1 = '蚨㡦Ɱ擳麗㾢鉦鵅' AND  ck0 = '\u0006yhs!byx5]'");
    execute("DELETE FROM %s USING TIMESTAMP 6 WHERE  pk0 = 1.0844396412062203E195 AND  pk1 = '蚨㡦Ɱ擳麗㾢鉦鵅' AND  ck0 = 'g3(X' + '\u0014\u000F'");
    execute("INSERT INTO %s (pk0, pk1, ck0, s1) VALUES (1.0844396412062203E195, '蚨㡦Ɱ擳麗㾢鉦鵅', '\u0002`\u0006' + '_7Us\u0016H5\u0005', true) USING TIMESTAMP 8");

    flush();

    ResultSet results = executeNetWithPaging("SELECT pk1, ck0, s1 FROM %s WHERE s1 = true AND v2 = 0x0000000000001d008e00000000000000 AND pk0 = 1.0844396412062203E195 ALLOW FILTERING", 100);
    assertRowsNet(results, row("蚨㡦Ɱ擳麗㾢鉦鵅", "Q", true));

//        pk0                    | pk1        | ck0 | s0                   | s1   | v0    | v1                   | v2                                 | v3                     | v4
//        1.0844396412062203E195 | '蚨㡦Ɱ擳麗㾢鉦鵅' | 'Q' | '14:59:24.557825178' | true | -2646 | -3909575580531410414 | 0x0000000000001d008e00000000000000 | 1.3611534850564156E135 | '0ch?bm[on]50h'
}

Found another seed that looks like the same kind of issue, but again, I cannot reproduce w/ a local CQLTester test:

Pure = true
Error: Unexpected results for query: SELECT * FROM ks1.tbl WHERE pk1 = 00000000-0000-1f00-ba00-000000000000 AND s0 = 0 ALLOW FILTERING
 

It's always possible there's a model issue of some kind, and I have had runs of over 10,000 seeds without error otherwise. Might need to focus energy on CASSANDRA-20323 or CASSANDRA-20260 where I have a non-fuzz repro...
